From: Dave Gerlach <d-gerlach@ti.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jan 2014 22:28:36 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 150/285] ARM: dts: am4372: Add voltage-tolerance to cpu0 node

Add missing voltage-tolerance entry for cpufreq to cpu0 at 2 percent
as am33xx does.

Signed-off-by: Dave Gerlach <d-gerlach@ti.com>
[Kevin: The original patch taken from TI
ti-sdk-am437x-evm-07.01.00.00-Linux-x86-Install.bin]
Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi
index 6f2151f..036c9a6 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi
@@ -47,6 +47,8 @@
 				1000000 1325000
 			>;
 
+			voltage-tolerance = <2>; /* 2 percentage */
+
 			platform-opp-modifier = <&mpu_opp_modifier>;
 
 			clocks = <&dpll_mpu_ck>;
